In [20]:
X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(X, y, test_size=0.20, random_state=42)
In [21]:
def evaluate(model, X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test):
    # Training the model
    model.fit(X_train, y_train)
    
    # Predicting on training and testing data
    y_test_pred = model.predict(X_test)
    y_train_pred = model.predict(X_train)

    print("TRAINING RESULTS: \n===============================")
    print(f"TRAINING R2 SCORE: {r2_score(y_train, y_train_pred):.4f}")
    print(f"TRAINING MEAN ABSOLUTE ERROR (MAE): {mean_absolute_error(y_train, y_train_pred):.4f}")
    print(f"TRAINING MEAN SQUARED ERROR (MSE): {mean_squared_error(y_train, y_train_pred):.4f}")
    print(f"TRAINING ROOT MEAN SQUARED ERROR (RMSE): {mean_squared_error(y_train, y_train_pred, squared=False):.4f}")

    print("\nTESTING RESULTS: \n===============================")
    print(f"TESTING R2 SCORE: {r2_score(y_test, y_test_pred):.4f}")
    print(f"TESTING MEAN ABSOLUTE ERROR (MAE): {mean_absolute_error(y_test, y_test_pred):.4f}")
    print(f"TESTING MEAN SQUARED ERROR (MSE): {mean_squared_error(y_test, y_test_pred):.4f}")
    print(f"TESTING ROOT MEAN SQUARED ERROR (RMSE): {mean_squared_error(y_test, y_test_pred, squared=False):.4f}")

Voting Regressor¶

In [34]:
from sklearn.ensemble import VotingRegressor, AdaBoostRegressor, BaggingRegressor
from sklearn.tree import DecisionTreeRegressor
import time


base_regressor = DecisionTreeRegressor()


clf1 = AdaBoostRegressor(n_estimators=100, random_state=0)
clf2 = BaggingRegressor(base_estimator=base_regressor)
clf3 = DecisionTreeRegressor()


eclf1 = VotingRegressor(estimators=[('ada', clf1), ('bg', clf2), ('dt', clf3)])


start_time = time.time()


eclf1.fit(X_train, y_train)


end_time = time.time()


vt_time = end_time - start_time
